-- Euro-Area Slump Deepens as Confidence Declines, Eurocoin Shows
-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 2012-04-27T07:33:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/euro-area-slump-deepens-as-confidence-declines-eurocoin-shows.html
The euro area’s economic slump
deepened in April on declining confidence among consumers and
executives, the  Eurocoin index  showed.  The gauge measuring economic activity in the 17-nation
region fell to minus 0.08 percent from minus 0.03 percent in
March, the London-based  Centre for Economic Policy Research  and
the  Bank of Italy , which co-produce the index, said today in an
e-mailed report.  “This result reflects the downturn in share prices and the
deterioration in consumer and business confidence, offset in
part, however, by the growth in exports,” the report said  To contact the reporter on this story:
